    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect normalization factor in dft3240 function\n\n### Summary\nThe dft3240 function in the OpenAirInterface 5G codebase was using an incorrect normalization factor, causing unexpected behavior when performing 3240-point FFT operations. The function was using a fixed normalization value from the dft_norm_table that was not appropriate for a 3240-point FFT.\n\nThis fix corrects the normalization factor used in the dft3240 function to properly scale the output according to the FFT size.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts_neon.c`: Updated normalization factor in dft3240 function from `dft_norm_table[14]` (18918) to correct value of 10, representing 1/3240 in Q15 fixed-point format.\n\n### Reproduction Steps\n1. Call the dft3240() function with any input data\n2. Observe that the output values are incorrectly scaled due to improper normalization\n3. The function uses sqrt(3) normalization instead of 1/3240 normalization, causing output values to be approximately 560 times larger than expected\n\nThe fix ensures that when scale_flag is set to 1, the output is properly normalized by 1/3240 instead of the incorrect sqrt(3) factor.\n"
}